	   <tr><td colspan=2>Read the posts in developers corner before posting info on what you think is correct. The post made by a station admin says nothing about level affecting the bonus a 2H weapon receives. The damage bonus was implemented to make 2H more attractive and competitive against dual wielding. If you have to swing an axe that requires 2 hands to lift up to swing using all your body...when it comes down it's going to do some serious damage. More so than just one arm swinging an axe at the same target. The damage bonus compensates for that. The longer the delay the harder it is to weild, therefore more mass and more damage when it hits. This thing has a delay of 46 and a weight of 3...course it is magical so that may account for the weight but the mass will still be enough to split a gnoll pup right down its center line. Im curious to see what the weighted axe will do damage of 45 and delay of 150....<br><br>Ithanis Xeres of Tunare<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
